'''Thontoros the Learned''', also called the '''Sage of the Just Gods''', was a [[sage]]. Thontoros made a study of the clergy, relics, and deeds of the followers of the deities of justice: [[Helm]], [[Ilmater]], [[Torm]], and [[Tyr]]. <ref group="note">The wording in ''Prayers from the Faithful'', "of other followers" suggests that Thontoros himself worshiped one of these four deities.

Thontoros once wrote about how the [[Twelve Champions of Torm]] defended the citadel of [[Lothtia]] on the [[Shining Plains]] against [[orc]]s in the [[1158 DR|Year of the Blood Tusk Charge, 1158]]. Thontoros mentioned that the [[paladin]] [[Harondath]] carried the holy shield the ''[[Veloghon of Vigilance]]'' in battle and "bathed it in the blood of the orcs of [[Thoktor Ironfangs]]."

Thontoros was the author of a book entitled ''[[Relics of the Righteous]]'', chronicling, amongst other things, the creation of the sword ''[[Dornavver]]''.
